  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Management Trainee",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p><strong>1. Sales & Marketing</strong></p><ul><li>Support the sales team with order processing, quotations, pricing updates, and customer coordination</li><li>Prepare sales reports, forecasts, and market analysis for management review</li><li>Liaise with customers on order status, delivery schedules, and documentation</li><li>Assist in improving sales processes and documentation workflows</li></ul><p><strong>2. Procurement </strong></p><ul><li>Assist in sourcing steel materials, spare parts, and services from local and overseas suppliers</li><li>Support supplier evaluation, price benchmarking, and negotiation preparation</li><li>Process purchase orders and track delivery timelines</li><li>Maintain procurement records and ensure compliance with company policies</li><li>Work with finance on invoice verification and payment tracking</li></ul><p><strong>3. Supply Chain </strong></p><ul><li>Support inventory planning, stock monitoring, and replenishment activities</li><li>Coordinate with warehouses, logistics providers, and internal stakeholders on shipment schedules</li><li>Assist in demand forecasting and supply planning activities</li><li>Analyse supply chain KPIs (e.g., lead time, stock turnover, service levels) and propose improvement initiatives</li><li>Participate in process improvement projects to enhance efficiency and reduce costs</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least Diploma in any discipline</li><li>Fresh graduates are welcome; prior internship experience in the steel or logistics industry is an advantage</li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Positive attitude, willingness to learn, and adaptability</li><li>Strong sense of responsibility and team-oriented mindset</li></ul>",
